==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Liquidation
<hw>Liq`ui*da"tion</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧k`w⟦icr⟧*d⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>liquidation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act
or process of liquidating; the state of being liquidated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To go into liquidation</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>to
turn over to a trustee one's assets and accounts, in order that the
several amounts of one's indebtedness may be authoritatively
ascertained, and that the assets may be applied toward their
discharge.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Liquidator</ent>⟦br⟧
